cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper focuses on explaining the predictions of black-box sequence-to-sequence models in natural language processing (NLP) tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses a variational autoencoder, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves solving a partitioning problem, which is a common topic in the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions testing their method on image captioning tasks, which falls under the sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper uses perturbed inputs to infer causal relationships, which is a technique commonly used in the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
